Rfmalloc bundles a patched copy of fmalloc as a vendored third-party component.

Bundled component: fmalloc
Upstream repository: https://github.com/yasukata/fmalloc
Vendored source directory: inst/fmalloc

fmalloc copyright:
- Kenichi Yasukata

fmalloc licensing:
- The fmalloc source files and COPYRIGHT notice state the Apache License,
  Version 2.0.
- See inst/fmalloc/COPYRIGHT and the upstream repository for the complete
  fmalloc license text and notices.

Bundled component: ptmalloc3
Upstream project: ptmalloc3 by Wolfram Gloger
Vendored source files: inst/fmalloc/ptmalloc3.c, inst/fmalloc/malloc-private.h,
  inst/fmalloc/sysdeps/*, and related support files

ptmalloc3 copyright:
- Wolfram Gloger

ptmalloc3 licensing:
- The bundled COPYRIGHT notice permits use, copying, modification,
  distribution, and sale under the conditions stated there.
- Some bundled GNU C Library support files carry GNU Lesser General Public
  License, version 2.1 or later, notices in their source headers.

Bundled component: Doug Lea malloc / dlmalloc
Upstream source: malloc-2.8.3
Vendored source files: inst/fmalloc/malloc.c and inst/fmalloc/malloc-2.8.3.h

Doug Lea malloc licensing:
- The bundled malloc.c and malloc-2.8.3.h source headers state that Doug Lea's
  malloc implementation was released to the public domain.

Rfmalloc package licensing:
- The Rfmalloc package code is licensed under GPL (>= 2), as declared in
  DESCRIPTION.
- This notice documents the bundled fmalloc/ptmalloc3/dlmalloc components and
  does not modify the license terms declared for the Rfmalloc package itself.
